ce:section.ce:para:
UV-light irradiation from the sunlight can generate hydroxyl radical molecules (HO
) [41]. The HO
molecules will attack the CC and CC bonds that are bonded to the aromatic rings at the centre of the MG structure to form intermediate products, as shown in Fig. 10 . MG structure is easily attacked by free radicals as its structure is not filled with a combination of aromatic rings like other organic dyes. Therefore, it is easily degraded once it is exposed to sunlight. However, the degradation rate was very slow, and the degradation efficiency was only about 58 %.
